Item.Name: LWM2M Security
Item.Description: This LwM2M Object provides the keying material of a LwM2M Client appropriate to access a specified LwM2M Server. One Object Instance SHOULD address a LwM2M Bootstrap-Server. These LwM2M Object Resources MUST only be changed by a LwM2M Bootstrap-Server or Bootstrap from Smartcard and MUST NOT be accessible by any other LwM2M Server.

Item.Name: LWM2M Security
Item.Description: This LwM2M Object provides the keying material of a LwM2M Client appropriate to access a specified LwM2M Server. One Object Instance SHOULD address a LwM2M Bootstrap-Server. These LwM2M Object Resources MUST only be changed by a LwM2M Bootstrap-Server or Bootstrap from Smartcard and MUST NOT be accessible by any other LwM2M Server.

Item.Name: LwM2M Server
Item.Description: This LwM2M Objects provides the data related to a LwM2M Server. A Bootstrap-Server has no such an Object Instance associated to it.

Item.Name: LwM2M Server
Item.Description: This LwM2M Objects provides the data related to a LwM2M Server. A Bootstrap-Server has no such an Object Instance associated to it.

Item.Name: LwM2M Access Control
Item.Description: It is used to check whether the LWM2M Server has access right for performing a operation.

Item.Name: Device
Item.Description: It provides a range of device related information which can be queried by the LWM2M Server, and a device reboot and factory reset function.

Item.Name: Device
Item.Description: It provides a range of device related information which can be queried by the LWM2M Server, and a device reboot and factory reset function.

Item.Name: Connectivity Monitoring
Item.Description: This LwM2M Object enables monitoring of parameters related to network connectivity. In this general connectivity Object, the Resources are limited to the most general cases common to most network bearers. It is recommended to read the description, which refers to relevant standard development organizations (e.g. 3GPP, IEEE). The goal of the Connectivity Monitoring Object is to carry information reflecting the more up to date values of the current connection for monitoring purposes. Resources such as Link Quality, Radio Signal Strength, Cell ID are retrieved during connected mode at least for cellular networks.

Item.Name: Connectivity Monitoring
Item.Description: This LwM2M Object enables monitoring of parameters related to network connectivity. In this general connectivity Object, the Resources are limited to the most general cases common to most network bearers. It is recommended to read the description, which refers to relevant standard development organizations (e.g. 3GPP, IEEE). The goal of the Connectivity Monitoring Object is to carry information reflecting the more up to date values of the current connection for monitoring purposes. Resources such as Link Quality, Radio Signal Strength, Cell ID are retrieved during connected mode at least for cellular networks.

Item.Name: Connectivity Monitoring
Item.Description: This LwM2M Object enables monitoring of parameters related to network connectivity. In this general connectivity Object, the Resources are limited to the most general cases common to most network bearers. It is recommended to read the description, which refers to relevant standard development organizations (e.g. 3GPP, IEEE). The goal of the Connectivity Monitoring Object is to carry information reflecting the more up to date values of the current connection for monitoring purposes. Resources such as Link Quality, Radio Signal Strength, Cell ID are retrieved during connected mode at least for cellular networks.

Item.Name: Firmware Update
Item.Description: It enables management of firmware which is to be updated. This Object includes installing firmware package, updating firmware, and performing actions after updating firmware

Item.Name: Location
Item.Description: It provides a range of device related information which can be queried by the LWM2M Server, and a device reboot and factory reset function.

Item.Name: Connectivity Statistics
Item.Description: This LWM2M Objects enables client to collect statistical information and enables the LWM2M Server to retrieve these information, set the collection duration and reset the statistical parameters.

Item.Name: Lock and Wipe
Item.Description: This LWM2M objects provides the resources needed to perform the lock and wipe operations

Item.Name: LWM2M Software Management
Item.Description: This LWM2M objects provides the resources needed to perform software management on the device. Each software component is managed via a dedicated Software Management Object instance

Item.Name: LWM2M Cellular Connectivity
Item.Description: This object specifies resources to enable a device to connect to a 3GPP or 3GPP2 bearer, including GPRS/EDGE, UMTS, LTE, NB-IoT, SMS. For cellular connectivity, this object focuses on Packet Switched (PS) connectivity and doesn't aim to provide comprehensive Circuit Switched (CS) connectivity management.

Item.Name: LWM2M APN Connection Profile
Item.Description: This object specifies resources to enable a device to connect to an APN.

Item.Name: WLAN connectivity
Item.Description: This object specifies resources to enable a device to connect to a WLAN bearer.

Item.Name: LWM2M Bearer Selection
Item.Description: This object specifies resources to enable a device to choose a PLMN/network on which to attach/register and what type of bearer to then connect. This object allows via remote bearer and network configuration to overwrite automatic network and bearer selection e.g. as supported by the UICC. An equivalent example for overwriting automatic selection is a user doing manual network and bearer selection on a smart phone.

Item.Name: LWM2M Software Component
Item.Description: The LWM2M software management object enables remote software management in M2M devices

Item.Name: DevCapMgmt
Item.Description: It manages the device capabilities of a device e.g. sensors, communication, etc.

Item.Name: Portfolio
Item.Description: The Portfolio Object allows to extend the data storage capability of other Object Instances in the LwM2M system, as well as the services which may be used to authenticate and to protect privacy of data contained in those extensions. In addition, a service of data encryption is also defined

Item.Name: Communications Characteristics
Item.Description: This object enables configuration of various generic communications parameters.

Item.Name: Non-Access Stratum (NAS) Configuration
Item.Description: This object provides Non-Access Stratum (NAS) configuration and is derived from 3GPP TS 24.368.

Item.Name: BinaryAppDataContainer
Item.Description: This LwM2M object provides the application service data related to a LwM2M Server, eg. Water meter data.

Item.Name: Event Log
Item.Description: The Event Log Object is a single Instance Object defined for logging data in a straightforward and generic way. The Resources of that Object are based on the OMA LwM2M set of reusable Resources dedicated to logging event activity.

Item.Name: LWM2M OSCORE
Item.Description: This LwM2M Object provides the keying material and related information of a LwM2M Client appropriate to access a specified LwM2M Server using OSCORE. One Object Instance MAY address a LwM2M Bootstrap-Server. These LwM2M Object Resources MUST only be changed by a LwM2M Bootstrap-Server or Bootstrap from Smartcard and MUST NOT be accessible by any other LwM2M Server. Instances of this Object are linked from Instances of Object 0 using the OSCORE Security Mode Resource of Object 0. Instances of this Object MUST NOT be linked from more than one Instance of Object 0.

Item.Name: Virtual Observe Notify
Item.Description: The Virtual Observe Notify Object provides a main function to notify multiple resources to a LwM2M Server in one notification message whether the resources are in one object/object instance or across multiple objects. The Virtual Observe Notify Object also provides some functions to implement more efficient multi-resource report.

Item.Name: CmdhPolicy
Item.Description: This Object provides links to a set of rules associated with a specific CSE that governs the behavior of that CSE regarding rejecting, buffering and sending request or response messages via the Mcc reference point.

Item.Name: ActiveCmdhPolicy
Item.Description: This Object provides a link to the currently active set of CMDH policies

Item.Name: CmdhDefaults
Item.Description: Defines which CMDH related parameters will be used by default.

Item.Name: CmdhDefEcValues
Item.Description: This Object represents default set of values for the Event Category parameter of an incoming request or response message.

Item.Name: CmdhEcDefParamValues
Item.Description: This Object represents a specific set of default values for the CMDH related parameters Request Expiration Timestamp, Result Expiration Timestamp, Operational Execution Time, Result Persistence and Delivery Aggregation that are applicable for a given Event Category if these parameters are not specified in the message.

Item.Name: CmdhLimits
Item.Description: This Object represents limits for CMDH related parameter values.

Item.Name: CmdhNetworkAccessRules
Item.Description: This Object defines the usage of underlying networks for forwarding information to other CSEs during processing of CMDH-related requests in a CSE.

Item.Name: CmdhNwAccessRule
Item.Description: This Object defines limits in usage of specific underlying networks for forwarding information to other CSEs during processing of CMDH-related requests in a CSE.

Item.Name: CmdhBuffer
Item.Description: This Object defines limits in usage of buffers for temporarily storing information that needs to be forwarded to other CSEs during processing of CMDH-related requests in a CSE.

Item.Name: CmdhBackOffParametersSet
Item.Description: This Object defines set of parameters which can be referenced by a specific Instance of the CmdhNwAccessRule Object (ID: 2055)

Item.Name: Digital Input
Item.Description: This IPSO object is a generic object that can be used with any kind of digital input interface. Specific objects for a given range of sensors are described later in the document, enabling to identify the type of sensors directly from its Object ID. This object may be used as a generic object if a dedicated one does not exist.

Item.Name: Digital Output
Item.Description: This IPSO object is a generic object that can be used with any kind of digital output interface. Specific object for a given range of sensors is described later in the document, enabling to identify the type of sensors directly from its Object ID. This object may be used as a generic object if a dedicated one does not exist.

Item.Name: Analog Input
Item.Description: This IPSO object is a generic object that can be used with any kind of analogue input interface. Specific object for a given range of sensors is described later in the document, enabling to identify the type of sensors directly from its Object ID. This object may be used as a generic object if a dedicated one does not exist.

Item.Name: Analog Output
Item.Description: This IPSO object is a generic object that can be used with any kind of analogue input interface. Specific object for a given range of sensors is described later in the document, enabling to identify the type of sensors directly from its Object ID. This object may be used as a generic object if a dedicated one does not exist.

Item.Name: Generic Sensor
Item.Description: This IPSO object allow the description of a generic sensor. It is based on the description of a value and a unit according to the SenML specification. Thus, any type of value defined within this specification can be reporting using this object. Specific object for a given range of sensors is described later in the document, enabling to identify the type of sensors directly from its Object ID. This object may be used as a generic object if a dedicated one does not exist.

Item.Name: Illuminance
Item.Description: This IPSO object should be used over a luminosity sensor to report a remote luminosity measurement. It also provides resources for minimum/maximum measured values and the minimum/maximum range that can be measured by the luminosity sensor. The unit used here is Lux.

Item.Name: Presence
Item.Description: This IPSO object should be used over a presence sensor to report a remote presence detection. It also provides resources to manage a counter, the type of sensor used (e.g the technology of the probe), and configuration for the delay between busy and clear detection state.

Item.Name: Temperature
Item.Description: This IPSO object should be used over a temperature sensor to report a remote temperature measurement. It also provides resources for minimum/maximum measured values and the minimum/maximum range that can be measured by the temperature sensor. The unit used here is degree Celsius.

Item.Name: Humidity
Item.Description: This IPSO object should be used over a humidity sensor to report a remote humidity measurement. It also provides resources for minimum/maximum measured values and the minimum/maximum range that can be measured by the humidity sensor. The unit used here is relative humidity as a percentage.

Item.Name: Power Measurement
Item.Description: This IPSO object should be used over a power measurement sensor to report a remote power measurement. It also provides resources for minimum/maximum measured values and the minimum/maximum range for both active and reactive power. It also provides resources for cumulative energy, calibration, and the power factor.

Item.Name: Actuation
Item.Description: This IPSO object is dedicated to remote actuation such as ON/OFF action or dimming. A multistate output can also be described as a string. This is useful to send pilot wire orders for instance. It also provides a resource to reflect the time that the device has been switched on.

Item.Name: Set Point
Item.Description: This IPSO object should be used to set a desired value to a controller, such as a thermostat. A special resource is added to set the colour of an object.

Item.Name: Load Control
Item.Description: This Object is used for demand-response load control and other load control in automation application (not limited to power).

Item.Name: Light Control
Item.Description: This Object is used to control a light source, such as a LED or other light. It allows a light to be turned on or off and its dimmer setting to be control as a % between 0 and 100.

Item.Name: Power Control
Item.Description: This Object is used to control a power source, such as a Smart Plug. It allows a power relay to be turned on or off and its dimmer setting to be control as a % between 0 and 100.

Item.Name: Accelerometer
Item.Description: This IPSO object can be used to represent a 1-3 axis accelerometer.

Item.Name: Magnetometer
Item.Description: This IPSO object can be used to represent a 1-3 axis magnetometer with optional compass direction.

Item.Name: Barometer
Item.Description: This IPSO object should be used with an air pressure sensor to report a remote barometer measurement. It also provides resources for minimum/maximum measured values and the minimum/maximum range that can be measured by the barometer sensor.

Item.Name: Voltage
Item.Description: This IPSO object should be used with voltmeter sensor to report measured voltage between two points. It also provides resources for minimum and maximum measured values, as well as the minimum and maximum range that can be measured by the sensor. An example measurement unit is volts.

Item.Name: Current
Item.Description: This IPSO object should be used with an ammeter to report measured electric current in amperes. It also provides resources for minimum and maximum measured values, as well as the minimum and maximum range that can be measured by the sensor. An example measurement unit is ampere.

Item.Name: Frequency
Item.Description: This IPSO object should be used to report frequency measurements. It also provides resources for minimum and maximum measured values, as well as the minimum and maximum range that can be measured by the sensor. An example measurement unit is hertz.

Item.Name: Depth
Item.Description: This IPSO object should be used to report depth measurements. It can, for example, be used to describe a generic rain gauge that measures the accumulated rainfall in millimetres (mm).

Item.Name: Percentage
Item.Description: This IPSO object should can be used to report measurements relative to a 0-100% scale. For example it could be used to measure the level of a liquid in a vessel or container in units of %.

Item.Name: Altitude
Item.Description: This IPSO object should be used with an altitude sensor to report altitude above sea level in meters. Note that Altitude can be calculated from the measured pressure given the local sea level pressure. It also provides resources for minimum and maximum measured values, as well as the minimum and maximum range that can be measured by the sensor. An example measurement unit is meters.

Item.Name: Load
Item.Description: This IPSO object should be used with a load sensor (as in a scale) to report the applied weight or force. It also provides resources for minimum and maximum measured values, as well as the minimum and maximum range that can be measured by the sensor.

Item.Name: Pressure
Item.Description: This IPSO object should be used to report pressure measurements. It also provides resources for minimum and maximum measured values, as well as the minimum and maximum range that can be measured by the sensor.

Item.Name: Loudness
Item.Description: This IPSO object should be used to report loudness or noise level measurements. It also provides resources for minimum and maximum measured values, as well as the minimum and maximum range that can be measured by the sensor.

Item.Name: Concentration
Item.Description: This IPSO object should be used to the particle concentration measurement of a medium. It also provides resources for minimum and maximum measured values, as well as the minimum and maximum range that can be measured by the sensor.

Item.Name: Acidity
Item.Description: This IPSO object should be used to report an acidity measurement of a liquid. It also provides resources for minimum and maximum measured values, as well as the minimum and maximum range that can be measured by the sensor.

Item.Name: Conductivity
Item.Description: This IPSO object should be used to report a measurement of the electric conductivity of a medium or sample. It also provides resources for minimum and maximum measured values, as well as the minimum and maximum range that can be measured by the sensor.

Item.Name: Power
Item.Description: This IPSO object should be used to report power measurements. It also provides resources for minimum and maximum measured values, as well as the minimum and maximum range that can be measured by the sensor.

Item.Name: Power Factor
Item.Description: This IPSO object should be used to report a measurement or calculation of the power factor of a reactive electrical load.

Item.Name: Distance
Item.Description: This IPSO object should be used to report a distance measurement. It also provides resources for minimum and maximum measured values, as well as the minimum and maximum range that can be measured by the sensor.

Item.Name: Energy
Item.Description: This IPSO object should be used to report energy consumption (Cumulative Power) of an electrical load.

Item.Name: Direction
Item.Description: This IPSO object is used to report the direction indicated by a compass, wind vane, or other directional indicator. The units of measure is plane angle degrees.

Item.Name: Time
Item.Description: This IPSO object is used to report the current time in seconds since January 1, 1970 UTC. There is also a fractional time counter that has a range of less than one second.

Item.Name: Gyrometer
Item.Description: This IPSO Object is used to report the current reading of a gyrometer sensor in 3 axes. It provides tracking of the minimum and maximum angular rate in all 3 axes.

Item.Name: Colour
Item.Description: This IPSO object should be used to report the measured value of a colour sensor in some colour space described by the units resource.

Item.Name: Location
Item.Description: This IPSO object represents GPS coordinates. This object is compatible with the LWM2M management object for location, but uses reusable resources.

Item.Name: Positioner
Item.Description: This IPSO object should be used with a generic position actuator with range from 0 to 100%.

Item.Name: Buzzer
Item.Description: This IPSO object should be used to actuate an audible alarm such as a buzzer, beeper, or vibration alarm.

Item.Name: Audio Clip
Item.Description: This IPSO object should be used for a speaker that plays a pre-recorded audio clip or an audio output that is sent elsewhere.

Item.Name: Timer
Item.Description: This IPSO object is used to time events and actions, using patterns common to industrial timers. A POST to the trigger resource or On/Off input state change starts the timing operation, and the timer remaining time shows zero when the operation is complete.

Item.Name: Addressable Text Display
Item.Description: This IPSO object is used to send text to a text-only or text mode graphics display.

Item.Name: On/Off switch
Item.Description: This IPSO object should be used with an On/Off switch to report the state of the switch.

Item.Name: Dimmer
Item.Description: This IPSO object should be used with a dimmer or level control to report the state of the control.

Item.Name: Up/Down Control
Item.Description: This IPSO object is used to report the state of an up/down control element like a pair of push buttons or a rotary encoder.

Item.Name: Multiple Axis Joystick
Item.Description: This IPSO object can be used to report the position of a shuttle or joystick control. A digital input is provided to report the state of an associated push button.

Item.Name: Rate
Item.Description: This object type should be used to report a rate measurement,

Item.Name: Push button
Item.Description: This IPSO object is used to report the state of a momentary action push button control and to count the number of times the control has been operated since the last observation.

Item.Name: Multi-state Selector
Item.Description: This IPSO object is used to represent the state of a multistate selector switch with a number of fixed positions.

Item.Name: Bitmap
Item.Description: Summarize several digital inputs to one value by mapping each bit to a digital input.

Item.Name: Stopwatch
Item.Description: An ascending timer that counts how long time has passed since the timer was started after reset.

Item.Name: powerupLog
Item.Description: One time event sent by the device at power up.

Item.Name: plmnSearchEvent
Item.Description: List of all PLMNs found during the initial search/scan

Item.Name: scellID
Item.Description: serving cell information that the RRC decides to camp on

Item.Name: cellReselectionEvent
Item.Description: cell reselection event information

Item.Name: handoverEvent
Item.Description: handover event information

Item.Name: radioLinkFailureEvent
Item.Description: Radio Link Failure Event

Item.Name: rrcStateChangeEvent
Item.Description: Current RRC state change information, including the event that triggered the state change

Item.Name: rrcTimerExpiryEvent
Item.Description: RRC timer expiry event information

Item.Name: cellBlacklistEvent
Item.Description: Cell blacklist information

Item.Name: esmContextInfo
Item.Description: ESM context information

Item.Name: emmStateValue
Item.Description: EMM context information

Item.Name: nasEmmTimerExpiryEvent
Item.Description: NAS EMM timer expiry information

Item.Name: nasEsmExpiryEvent
Item.Description: NAS ESM timer expiry information

Item.Name: emmFailureCauseEvent
Item.Description: Triggered at EMM failure - failure cause is logged

Item.Name: rachLatency_delay
Item.Description: RACH Latency and delay information

Item.Name: macRachAttemptEvent
Item.Description: RACH information. Logged at RACH TX

Item.Name: macRachAttemptReasonEvent
Item.Description: RACH Information - reason for initiating RACH

Item.Name: macTimerStatusEvent
Item.Description: MAC timer expiry information

Item.Name: macTimingAdvanceEvent
Item.Description: Timing advance information

Item.Name: ServingCellMeasurement
Item.Description: Serving Cell Measurement

Item.Name: NeighborCellMeasurements
Item.Description: Neighbor Cell Measurements

Item.Name: TimingAdvance
Item.Description: Neighbor Cell Measurements

Item.Name: txPowerHeadroomEvent
Item.Description: TX power headroom information

Item.Name: radioLinkMonitoring
Item.Description: Radio Link monitoring information maintained by RRC

Item.Name: PagingDRX
Item.Description: Paging DRX information

Item.Name: txPowerBackOffEvent
Item.Description: TX Power backoff information

Item.Name: Message3Report
Item.Description: RACH message 3 report information

Item.Name: PbchDecodingResults
Item.Description: Serving cell PBCH decoding information

Item.Name: pucchPowerControl
Item.Description: PUCCH TX power control information

Item.Name: PrachReport
Item.Description: PRACH report information. Deprecated by v2.0.

Item.Name: PrachReport
Item.Description: PRACH report information

Item.Name: VolteCallEvent
Item.Description: VoLTE call status

Item.Name: SipRegistrationEvent
Item.Description: SIP Registration status

Item.Name: sipPublishEvent
Item.Description: SIP Publish status

Item.Name: sipSubscriptionEvent
Item.Description: SIP Subscription status

Item.Name: volteCallStateChangeEvent
Item.Description: VoLTE call status change

Item.Name: VoLTErtpPacketLoss
Item.Description: Log is generated at the receiving end of RTP flow when newReceivedSequenceNumber - lastReceivedSequenceNumber > 1

Item.Name: oA Basic Control
Item.Description: The 'oA Basic Control' represents a common basic interface for a Control Function. This allows to have vendor specific (executing) control functions using diverse object numbers to be interfaced for the basic functionality in a common way. The object provides the basic functionality required for an OpenAIS control object.

Item.Name: oA Device
Item.Description: The 'oA Device' represents the OpenAIS specific parameters of a Device that are necessary in addition to the LWM2M Device.

Item.Name: oA Group
Item.Description: The 'oA Group' represents a group. It contains an application group ID, a security group ID and a list of multicast and unicast IP addresses that are used in the group. \nAdditionally it contains a list of all members of the group.

Item.Name: oA Logical Colour Light-Point Actuator
Item.Description: The 'oA Logical Colour Light Point Actuator' represents the logical part of an actuator model for a colour light point. The corresponding physical device is a light channel and associated gear (e.g. LED driver).\nThe Object (module) supports several interactions that include absolute and relative colour setting. Several device configuration parameters are mapped, which relate to behaviour or describe device limitations.

Item.Name: oA Logical Colour Temperature Light-Point Actuator
Item.Description: The 'oA Logical Colour Temperature Light Point Actuator' represents the logical part of an actuator model for a tunable white light point. The corresponding physical device is a light channel and associated gear (e.g. LED driver).\nThe Object (module) supports several interactions that include absolute and relative colour temperature setting. Several device configuration parameters are mapped, which relate to behaviour or describe device limitations. Note that the overall intensity is not controlled by this object, it remains controlled by a logical light point object to ease dimming action across tuneable, coloured and non coloured lights. Please note also, that the corresponding executing object does not need to be restricted to tuneable white operation.

Item.Name: oA Logical Illuminance Sensor
Item.Description: The 'oA Logical Illuminance Sensor' represents the logical part of an illuminance sensor. The corresponding physical device is a sensor that detects illuminance in its detection area.

Item.Name: oA Logical Light-Point Actuator
Item.Description: The 'oA Logical Light Point Actuator' represents the logical part of an actuator model for a dimmable light point. The corresponding physical device is a light channel and associated gear (e.g. LED driver).\nThe Object (module) supports several interactions that include basic On/Off as well as Up/Down dimming. Several device configuration parameters are mapped, which relate to behaviour or describe device limitations. For multi-channel luminaires where the configuration per channel may vary significantly (e.g. different max/min values), multiple instances of this Object should be used.

Item.Name: oA Logical Presence Sensor
Item.Description: The 'oA Logical Presence Sensor' represents the logical part of a presence sensor. The corresponding physical device is a sensor that detects presence in its detection area. \nThe Object supports two states 'presence' and 'absence'.

Item.Name: oA Logical Push-Button Sensor
Item.Description: The 'oA Logical Push-Button Sensor' represents the logical part of a standard, normally open, push-button input. The corresponding physical device is a button with a spring that returns the button to the un-pushed state once it is released. \nThe Object supports several events such as 'click', 'hold', 'double-click' and 'release'. It also indicates if the button is 'stuck'. For physical devices with multiple push-button inputs, an instance of this Object is required to map each input.

Item.Name: oA Physical Colour Light-Point Actuator
Item.Description: The 'oA Physical Colour Light-Point Actuator' represents a physical colour light-point actuator. It is necessary to map at least on Logical Light Point Actuator to control the intensity and one Logical Colour Light-Point to control the colour to the Physical Colour Light-Point.

Item.Name: oA Physical Colour Temperature Light-Point Actuator
Item.Description: The 'oA_Physical Colour Temperature Light-Point Actuator' represents a physical tunable white light-point actuator. It is necessary to map at least on Logical Light Point Actuator to control the intensity and one Logical Colour Temperature Light-Point to control the colour temperature to the Physical Colour Temperature Light Point.

Item.Name: oA Physical Illuminance Sensor
Item.Description: The 'oA Physical Light-Point Actuator' represents a physical light-point actuator. All logical light-point actuators (object instances of 'oA Light-Point Actuator') are mapped to one physical light-point actuator.

Item.Name: oA Physical Light-Point Actuator
Item.Description: The 'oA Physical Illuminance Sensor' represents the physical part of an illuminance sensor. All logical illuminance sensors (object instances of 'oA Illuminance Sensor') are mapped to one physical illuminance sensor.

Item.Name: oA Physical Presence Sensor
Item.Description: The 'oA Physical Presence Sensor' represents the physical part of a presence sensor. All logical presence sensors (object instances of 'oA Presence Sensor') are mapped to one physical presence sensor

Item.Name: oA Physical Push-Button Sensor
Item.Description: The 'oA Physical Push-Button Sensor' represents the physical part of a push-button sensor. All logical push-button sensors (object instances of 'oA Push-Button Sensor') are mapped to one physical push-button sensor.

Item.Name: oA Receiving Object
Item.Description: The 'oA Receiving Object' provides a resource for sensors/actuators to report their status message to. It is used with control objects as logical object that forwards the sensor and status data to the executing object. \nIt is also used to receive the 'go bootstrap' message, using the Struct-ID 255, in OOTB mode.

Item.Name: oA Reporting Object
Item.Description: The 'oA Reporting Object' packs several status messages available at the node into a single, size optimized message, as e.g. used with data collect or BMS interfacing.

Item.Name: oA Scene
Item.Description: The 'oA Scene' represents a scene model. The scene holds defined values for each actuator in one group.

Item.Name: oA OGC-Security
Item.Description: The 'oA Security' provides the keying material of a LWM2M Client appropriate to access a specified LWM2M Server in context of OpenAIS. One Object Instance SHOULD address a LWM2M Bootstrap Server. \nThese LWM2M Object Resources MUST only be changed by a LWM2M Bootstrap Server or Bootstrap from Smartcardand MUST NOT be accessible by any other LWM2M Server.

Item.Name: oA Status Report Structure
Item.Description: The 'oA Status Report Structure' describes the content of the status reports. Its ID is always the first byte, the following bytes are defined by Keys.

Item.Name: Smoke Alarm
Item.Description: This is an alarm that should be raised if the meter detects CO2 concentration above a pre-configured threshold.

Item.Name: Manhole Cover
Item.Description: Describe the status of a manhole cover.

Item.Name: TBC
Item.Description: TBC

Item.Name: HostDeviceInfo
Item.Description: This LWM2M Object provides a range of host device related information which can be queried by the LWM2M Server. The host device is any integrated device with an embedded cellular radio module.

Item.Name: 3-Phase Power Meter
Item.Description: This Object provides the information to represent a generic 3-Phase Power Meter

Item.Name: Single-Phase Power Meter
Item.Description: This Object provides the information to represent a generic Single-Phase Power Meter

Item.Name: VehicleControlUnit
Item.Description: This Object provides the information to represent a generic VCU (vehicle control unit)

Item.Name: Relay Management
Item.Description: This LWM2M Object provides a range of eNB related measurements and parameters of which several are changeable. Furthermore, it includes Resources to enable/disable the eNB

Item.Name: CrowdBox Measurements
Item.Description: This LWM2M Object provides CrowdBox-related measurements such as serving cell parameters, backhaul timing advance, and neighbour cell reports.

Item.Name: Neighbour Cell Report
Item.Description: This LWM2M Object provides the neighbour cell report. The CrowdBox Measurements Object and the Connected UE Report Object have both Objlnk Resources pointing to this Object

Item.Name: Connected UE Measurements
Item.Description: This LWM2M Object provides a range of measurements of connected UEs and provides an Object link to the Connected UE report.

Item.Name: Connected UE Report
Item.Description: This LWM2M Object provides a range of information related to the connected UEs.

Item.Name: App Data Container
Item.Description: This LWM2M Object is used for reporting application data of a device.

Item.Name: AT Command
Item.Description: Used to execute an AT command on a cellular modem

Item.Name: Manifest
Item.Description: This object provides a range of information related to updating packages on a device

Item.Name: Confidential Data
Item.Description: This LWM2M Object is used for reporting data, but in a confidential way

Item.Name: Current Loop Input
Item.Description: This LwM2M Object provides a representation of a current loop sensor, which indicates the value emitted by a current source.

Item.Name: Device Metadata
Item.Description: This object provides a range of information related to device metadata

Item.Name: ECID-Signal Measurement Information
Item.Description: This LWM2M Object provides ECID signal measurements of a device.

Item.Name: Heat / Cooling meter
Item.Description: This Object provides the information to represent a generic (district) heat or cooling meter

Item.Name: Current Loop Output
Item.Description: This LWM2M Object provides a representation of a current loop source, which may be used to carry control signals.

Item.Name: System Log
Item.Description: This object provides read access to log buffers as well as limited configuration of logging services.

Item.Name: Runtime Database
Item.Description: This object allows manipulation of Runtime Database variables. Object deprecated with version 2.0 due to incorrect Type/Operation combination.

Item.Name: RDB
Item.Description: This object allows manipulation of Runtime Database variables.

Item.Name: Interval Data Delivery
Item.Description: The Interval Data Delivery object provides an optimised means for managing the delivery of interval data from multiple Interval Data Object instances.

Item.Name: Event Data Delivery
Item.Description: The Event Data Delivery object provides a simple means for managing the delivery of event data from multiple Event Data Object instances.

Item.Name: Delivery Schedule
Item.Description: The Delivery Schedule object provides a means for controlling the periodic delivery of interval and event data to the LwM2M server.

Item.Name: Leakage Detection Configuration
Item.Description: The leakage detection configuration object provides a means for configuring the timing and sampling frequency of a vibration based network leak detector

Item.Name: Water Flow Readings
Item.Description: Measures the flow of water in regular intervals

Item.Name: Daily Maximum Flow Rate Readings
Item.Description: Measures the maximum flow rate and its time stamp for specified period

Item.Name: Temperature Readings
Item.Description: Periodic temperature measurements

Item.Name: Pressure Readings
Item.Description: Periodic pressure measurements

Item.Name: Battery Level Readings
Item.Description: Periodic battery level measurements

Item.Name: Communications Activity Time Readings
Item.Description: Measures the total duration that the meter was activating its radio for packet transmission or receipt for the period. Used to monitor for excess poower usage over time.

Item.Name: Water Meter Customer Leakage Alarm
Item.Description: A binary flag indicating continual usage (e.g. greater than 5 L/h for 24 hours and the flow never returning to zero at any time).

Item.Name: Water Meter Reverse Flow Alarm
Item.Description: An alarm indicating reverse flow through the pipe. Also supports delivery of the approximate volume of water flowing in the reverse direction in the preceding period.

Item.Name: Water Meter Empty Pipe Alarm
Item.Description: An alarm when meter detects there is no liquid in the pipe

Item.Name: Water Meter Tamper Alarm
Item.Description: Detects interference from strong magnetic field or other electrical sources. If this is not relevant for ultrasonic meters then the tamper alarm may be used to indicate someone attempting to open the physical enclosure or other options the manufacturer may present.

Item.Name: Water Meter High Pressure Alarm
Item.Description: Where supported by the meter this is an alarm that should be raised if the meter detects pressure above a pre-configured threshold.

Item.Name: Water Meter Low Pressure Alarm
Item.Description: Where supported by the meter this is an alarm that should be raised if the meter detects pressure below a pre-configured threshold.

Item.Name: High Temperature Alarm
Item.Description: Where supported by the meter this is an alarm that should be raised if the meter detects temperature above a pre-configured threshold. When the temperature drops below the clear threshold, the alarm should be cleared.

Item.Name: Low Temperature Alarm
Item.Description: Where supported by the meter this is an alarm that should be raised if the meter detects temperature below a pre-configured threshold. When the temperature rises above the clear threshold, the alarm should be cleared

Item.Name: Water Network Leak Alarm
Item.Description: All meters must support the following default configuration. This alarm will be based on the frequency output of the vibration sensor/accelerometer on the SEW Daughter board. When a frequency is identified that has the characteristics of an upstream network leak, and its amplitude is above the defined threshold, the meter will report this as a network leak alarm.

Item.Name: Low Battery Alarm
Item.Description: This Alarm is raised when the battery voltage drops below a defined level

Item.Name: Daughter Board Failure Alarm
Item.Description: This binary status should indicate that the meter MCU can no longer communicate with a daughter board

Item.Name: Device Reboot Event
Item.Description: This binary status should indicate that the meter MCU can no longer communicate with a daughter board

Item.Name: Time Synchronisation Event
Item.Description: This event records the fact that the device has rebooted

Item.Name: App Fota Container
Item.Description: This LWM2M Object is used to download the firmware package of a device's application.

Item.Name: Voltage Logging
Item.Description: Periodic voltage measurements that are logged into CBOR structure payload.

Item.Name: Voltage Transient
Item.Description: Object for sampling high frequency values (in this case Voltage readings) in order to aggregate them and summarize them (Avg, Max, Min) and to then time-stamp and log these aggregates for packaging and transmission to the server. This allows for efficient data transfer of high frequency data, without the need to send huge amounts of raw data over the air.

Item.Name: Pressure Transient
Item.Description: Object for measuring high frequency pressure readings and summarizing/logging them at defined intervals. This way, the raw data does not need to be sent over the air, and instead just the Average , Maximum and Minimum values for the interval

Item.Name: HostDevice
Item.Description: This LWM2M Object provides a range of host device related information which can be queried by the LWM2M Server. The host device is any integrated device with an embedded cellular radio module.

Item.Name: LWM2M Meta Object
Item.Description: Use this meta object to provide one or more locations hosting XML data model definitions for reusable or private and vendor-specific devices, such as those in the range 26241-42768.

Item.Name: Solar Radiation
Item.Description: This object is used to report solar irradiance (SI), i.e. power per unit area received from the Sun in the form of electromagnetic radiation, on a planar surface measured by a pyranometer or similar instrument. A pyranometer measures solar irradiance from the hemisphere above within a wavelength range 0.3 m to 3 m. For example, the application of solar radiation measurement can be meteorological networks and solar energy applications.

Item.Name: Gas Readings
Item.Description: Object to periodically log readings from any gas sensor (eg H2S, VOCx, methane etc)

Item.Name: Particulates
Item.Description: This object should be used to report the concentration of particulates, for example a measurement of a particulates air quality sensor. It also provides resources for minimum/maximum measured values and the minimum/maximum range that can be measured by the particulate sensor. An example measurement unit is microgrammes per cubic metre ug/m3.
